📊 Improving Data Accuracy in CRM using AI
📌 Project Overview
Customer Relationship Management (CRM) systems often contain inaccurate or duplicate data, leading to inefficiencies in business operations. This project leverages AI-driven techniques to improve data accuracy in CRM by detecting anomalies, filtering incorrect entries, and enhancing overall data reliability.

🚀 Features
AI-Powered Anomaly Detection: Identifies incorrect, duplicate, or suspicious data.
Data Accuracy Visualization: Graphical insights into CRM data accuracy improvements.
Confusion Matrix Evaluation: Assessing the model's performance in detecting errors.
User-Friendly Dashboard: Upload and analyze CRM datasets with interactive charts.
Automated Data Cleaning: Improves CRM data accuracy through AI-based filtering.
🖼️ Visualizations
🔹 Confusion Matrix for AI Model Evaluation

This matrix demonstrates the performance of the AI model in detecting accurate and incorrect records.
🔹 CRM Data Accuracy Dashboard

A dashboard that allows users to upload CRM data and analyze its accuracy using AI.
🔹 CRM Data Accuracy Pie Chart

A pie chart visualization showing the proportion of accurate vs. incorrect CRM data.
⚙️ Technologies Used
Python (Data Processing & AI)
Machine Learning (Anomaly Detection)
Matplotlib & Seaborn (Data Visualization)
Flask/Django (Web Dashboard)
Pandas & NumPy (Data Handling)
📂 Installation & Setup
Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/CRM-Data-Accuracy-AI.git
cd CRM-Data-Accuracy-AI
Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the application:

Copy
Edit
python app.py
Upload your CRM dataset and analyze the accuracy.
📈 Results & Insights
The AI model successfully improved CRM data accuracy from 80% to 83.5%.
Anomalies in the CRM dataset were identified and categorized for correction.
The system provides real-time insights and data cleansing recommendations.
